## Subprocess LLM Access
Pipeline scripts can access LLM from subprocess via `qwenpaw agents chat`:
```python
import subprocess
r = subprocess.run([
    "qwenpaw", "agents", "chat",
    "--from-agent", "default",
    "--to-agent", "default",
    "--text", prompt
], capture_output=True, text=True, timeout=120)
response = r.stdout
# Extract response after "]  " separator
```
- Calls internal QwenPaw API (localhost:8088) → routes to LLM backend (Sumopod)
- Used by `auto_news_pipeline.py` v4 for KPIG article writing
- Fallback to template if LLM fails (empty/timeout/garbled output)

